---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout title="Community" description="Join the Sportlad Telegram community — free banter group and paid picks group. Real accountability, no fake personas.">
  <h1 style="margin-top: 32px;">Community</h1>
  <p style="color: var(--muted); max-width: 60ch;">
    This is the whole point of Sportlad — a real community around real opinions and real accountability, not a tips-bot with a logo.
  </p>

  <div class="section-head"><h2>Join Telegram</h2></div>
  <div class="card-grid">
    <div class="card">
      <span class="tag education">Free</span>
      <h3>Free Group</h3>
      <p>General banter, free tip of the week, article announcements, new member welcomes, Q&amp;A.</p>
      <a class="btn ghost" style="margin-top: 12px;" href="#">Join free group →</a>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <span class="tag">£20/mo</span>
      <h3>Paid Group</h3>
      <p>Daily picks feed, Wins &amp; Losses thread, live matchday threads, monthly "why we got it wrong" retro.</p>
      <a class="btn" style="margin-top: 12px;" href="/tips/#join">Join paid group →</a>
    </div>
  </div>
  <p style="color: var(--muted); font-size: 0.85rem;">(Telegram invite links go live at launch — swap the placeholders above once your groups are set up.)</p>

  <div class="section-head" id="rules"><h2>House Rules</h2></div>
  <div class="tool-card">
    <p><strong>Banter's welcome, abuse isn't.</strong> Slag off a team all you like, don't slag off a person.</p>
    <p><strong>No touting, no begging for tips.</strong> This is a community, not a market stall.</p>
    <p><strong>Ask me anything, genuinely.</strong> Weekly scheduled AMA slot — plus I'm in the group day to day, not posting-and-vanishing.</p>
    <p><strong>Struggling, or it's stopped being fun?</strong> Tell me, or just leave — no judgement, ever.</p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0;"><a href="/takes/">Full house rules doc →</a></p>
  </div>

  <div class="section-head" id="chris"><h2>Meet Chris</h2></div>
  <div class="tool-card">
    <p>Sportlad's got one real voice, and it's mine. No fictional tipsters, no invented personas, no "our team of experts" nonsense — every take and every pick has my name on it, and when I get one wrong, I'll say so.</p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0;">That's the whole positioning: paid to be right, not paid by a bookie to send you somewhere.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="section-head"><h2>What Makes This Feel Real</h2></div>
  <div class="card-grid">
    <div class="card"><h3>Weekly AMA</h3><p>Scheduled, not sporadic — same slot every week.</p></div>
    <div class="card"><h3>New Member Shoutouts</h3><p>Every new member gets a proper welcome, not a bot message.</p></div>
    <div class="card"><h3>Bad Beat of the Week</h3><p>Community-voted worst loss — commiserate together, don't just eat it alone.</p></div>
    <div class="card"><h3>Voice Notes</h3><p>30-60 second voice notes on the bigger picks — you get to hear the confidence, not just read it.</p></div>
  </div>
</Layout>
